        {
            "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
            "body": "> Is there an actual problem besides the fact that this code is executed?\r\n\r\nYes, if you use a statusline that redraws frequently (e.g. 100ms) and you are getting constant LSP diagnostic updates there is visible flickering. \r\n\r\nExample:\r\n\r\nhttps://github.com/user-attachments/assets/e387ac51-0b9a-43a0-871a-ee652cd450e8\r\n\r\nMy actual config with `rust_analyzer` attached to two buffers in a large project:\r\n\r\nhttps://github.com/user-attachments/assets/0d5c407c-7781-4c22-b965-aedbb3329e62\r\n\r\nI know a repro without plugins would be ideal, I'll try to come up with something. If autocmd windows *should* be able to have statuslines, I can create an issue related to the diagnostic part of the problem.",
