        },
        {
            "author_association": "MEMBER",
            "body": "> I think because aucmd_win windows are removed from the grid before they can be shown to the user. \r\n\r\nSo from those gifs this doesn't appear to be the case, which seems problematic. I wonder if we should update the redraw/statusline code to skip over hidden windows and set `WinConfig.hide` in `win_alloc_aucmd_win()`, rather than update various APIs.",
            "created_at": "2026-05-25T11:56:03Z",
            "html_url": "https://github.com/neovim/neovim/pull/39983#issuecomment-4534054820",
            "id": 4534054820,
            "issue_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/neovim/neovim/issues/39983",
            "node_id": "IC_kwDOAPphoM8AAAABDkAvpA",
            "performed_via_github_app": null,
