        {
            "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
            "body": "A minimal example that produces flickering even with `nvim --clean`:\r\n\r\n```lua\r\nvim.diagnostic.config({})\r\n\r\nlocal buf = vim.api.nvim_get_current_buf()\r\nlocal other_bufs = {}\r\nfor i = 1, 5 do\r\n  local other_buf = vim.api.nvim_create_buf(true, true)\r\n  table.insert(other_bufs, other_buf)\r\n  vim.api.nvim_buf_set_lines(other_buf, 0, -1, true, { 'hello', 'from', 'the', 'other', 'buf :-)' })\r\nend\r\n\r\nlocal timer = vim.uv.new_timer()\r\ntimer:start(\r\n  0,\r\n  250,\r\n  vim.schedule_wrap(function()\r\n    for _, other_buf in ipairs(other_bufs) do\r\n      vim.api.nvim_exec_autocmds('DiagnosticChanged', {\r\n        buf = other_buf,\r\n      })\r\n    end\r\n  end)\r\n)\r\n```",
